May relate to confusion of meaning in English between leg (whole limb) and leg (part between knee and ankle). If refer to whole limb, may be that failure to recognise thigh and leg as separate parts was confined to west coast people. Use of distinct words for thigh and leg by most of tribes and distinctness in words for other parts of limb indicate that Tasmanians had clear idea of separate parts of lower limb
